Package com.hyperwallet.android.exception

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProviderException
    An instance of HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenProviderException is created to comply with the ExceptionMapper interface when an authentication token retrieval fails and the HyperwalletAuthenticationTokenListener.onFailure(UUID, String) is called.
    HyperwalletException
    This exception is thrown when an issue is detected during the processing of a request to the Hyperwallet Core SDK.
    HyperwalletGqlException
    Indicates an exceptional condition that occurred while executing a GraphQL transaction with the Hyperwallet platform.
    HyperwalletInitializationException
    Thrown when retrieving an uninitialized Hyperwallet instance from Hyperwallet.getDefault().
    HyperwalletInvalidRequestPathException
    Exception thrown when passing an invalid path to the http request.
    HyperwalletJsonParseException
    Exception type thrown when parsing JSON responses from API has errors
    HyperwalletRequestNotBuiltException
    Request is null or not built
    HyperwalletRestException
    Indicates an exceptional condition that occurred while executing a REST transaction with the Hyperwallet platform.
